problem: On planet Larky, 7 ligs = 4 lags, and 9 lags = 20 lugs. How many ligs are equivalent to 80 lugs?
solution: Multiply the second equation by 4 to find that 36 lags are equivalent to 80 lugs.  Then multiply the first equation by 9 to find that 36 lags are equivalent to 63 ligs.  Since each is equivalent to 36 lags, 80 lugs and $\boxed{63}$ ligs are equivalent.
model_solution:
First step: 80 lugs = (9 lags/20 lags) × 80 lugs
Second step: (9 lags/20 lags) × 80 lugs = 36 lags
Third step: 36 lags = (7 ligs / 4 lags) × 36 lags
(7 ligs / 4 lags) × 36 lags = 63 ligs
Fourth step: 63 ligs 

(No, this is not the final step.)
Fifth step: 63 ligs = (7 ligs / 4 lags) × (9 lags / 20 lags) × 80 lugs
63 ligs = (7 ligs / 4 lags) × (9 lags / 20 lags) × 80 lugs = (7/4) × (9/20) × 80 ligs = (7 × 9) × (80/40) ligs 
= 63 × 2 ligs 
= 126 ligs
